<br>
I wish they'd come out with a demo version so I could check it out myself. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ubulvyne.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bulvyne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 241<br> <font color=#E9D756>(5/17/02 9:03:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9606.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: combat?</span><hr size=1> You can 'slash', 'chop', and 'thrust'.<br>
<br>
Weapons all do different amounts of damage based on which type of attack you use.  Some weapons are better for one type of attack than others.<br>
<br>
There is no &quot;dual wielding&quot;. <br>
There are two-handed weapons (Claymores, etc).<br>
You can throw daggers/throwing stars.<br>
You can shoot a bow (arrows actually 'sink' towards the ground as they fly).<br>
<br>
And of course, a bazillion magic-attacks/spells.<br>
<br>
